The paper presents a watermarking scheme based on Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) for images, which is a common technique used in computer vision and image processing (cs.CV). The scheme also includes a hash-based watermarking scheme for further security, which involves cryptography and information theory (cs.CR, cs.IT). The paper also discusses the security analysis of the scheme, which involves machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG, cs.MM).
